<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/438363-after-all-the-mysteries-have-been-solved-i">After all the mysteries have been solved I am left behind with one last question. What does &#39;Iadadoveandasweedovedied&#39; on page 217 of my copy mean? Was it Christie&#39;s short flirt with Dadaism or even Surrealism? Or could it be a recite from Keats or Shelly as suggested in the text. If anyone can help me out here, where Hercule Poirot left of, I be most thankful.</a>
</div>
