<div id="review_1621958500" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1621958500" />
    <a title="Sumit RK" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38271102-sumit-rk"><img alt="Sumit RK" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599896274p2/38271102.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1621958500?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sumit RK" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sumit RK" href="/user/show/38271102-sumit-rk">Sumit RK</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1621958500" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18027764509379410486">Compared to the other Christie mysteries, this was just OK.<br/>Pros: 1.The story itself was quite good; set in foreign locales that added to the mystery. <br/>Cons: 1. All characters felt one dimensional &amp; unbearable.<br/> 2.No Poirot in almost the first half &amp; the built up takes so much of time. <br/> 3. Poirot&apos;s deduction &amp; his explanation is confusing and the final twist was totally bizarre. <br/> It was totally unexpected, but it didn&apos;t make sense. <br/>So in short, &quot;Appointment with Death&quot; was a fast read but underwhel</span>
  <span id="freeText18027764509379410486" style="display:none">Compared to the other Christie mysteries, this was just OK.<br />Pros: 1.The story itself was quite good; set in foreign locales that added to the mystery. <br />Cons: 1. All characters felt one dimensional &amp; unbearable.<br /> 2.No Poirot in almost the first half &amp; the built up takes so much of time. <br /> 3. Poirot's deduction &amp; his explanation is confusing and the final twist was totally bizarre. <br /> It was totally unexpected, but it didn't make sense. <br />So in short, "Appointment with Death" was a fast read but underwhelming &amp; disappointing. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18027764509379410486" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

