<span id="freeTextContainer17559310146907004430">The Boyntons are a strange family. Unlike the other guests in their Jerusalem hotel they all seem unhappy &amp; nervous. Old Mrs Boynton seems to have a strange hold over all of them. When the old lady is found dead little Belgian detective Hercule Poirot sets out to find if it was murder &amp; (if it was) who committed the crime. <br/>This is a pretty straightforward Agatha Christie novel, but I really liked the solution which once again I failed to solve. My only criticism was that Christie could have made</span>
  <span id="freeText17559310146907004430" style="display:none">The Boyntons are a strange family. Unlike the other guests in their Jerusalem hotel they all seem unhappy &amp; nervous. Old Mrs Boynton seems to have a strange hold over all of them. When the old lady is found dead little Belgian detective Hercule Poirot sets out to find if it was murder &amp; (if it was) who committed the crime. <br />This is a pretty straightforward Agatha Christie novel, but I really liked the solution which once again I failed to solve. My only criticism was that Christie could have made a lot more use of the exotic location than she did.</span>
